      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's more than just \"comfort\" or \"professionalism\" though. i've noticed it's specifically these high-contrast, repetitive geometric patterns. it's like they're designed to hijack your brain's processing. i read somewhere about how certain visual frequencies can induce a trance-like state or make people more suggestible. don't you think it's weird how they're so prevalent in mass-produced clothes right now?",
